summary: Peter literally means so much to Tony that this teenage boy, who lost both his parents, lost his uncle, got gifts from a spider...
body:
Peter literally means so much to Tony that this teenage boy, who lost both his parents, lost his uncle, got gifts from a spider bite and personally took on the responsiblity to protect citizens as The Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man, was recruited to fight in a civil war alongside and against the superheroes he has looked up to, was given a new suit and learned that to be a superhero it’s not the suit that makes the superhero it’s the person who wears it, risked everything to help Tony fight Thanos on Titan despite only being a kid, and who clung onto his surrogate father scared and hurt only to vanish in his arms, was Tony’s main motivation throughout Endgame.

Iron-Dad for the win man.

summary: Brie Larson has such a friendly and warm smile?  Like her eyes are so kind, her face is just so round and glowing, and she just...
body:
Brie Larson has such a friendly and warm smile? 

Like her eyes are so kind, her face is just so round and glowing, and she just seems like genuine when she’s smiling?

She wrecked me during Captain Marvel when she smiled at Stan Lee?

She destroyed me when she smiled so kindly, in the middle of the biggest fight of their lives, at Peter Parker, a teenage boy who’s doing his Best, but is still nervous enough to be awed by Captain Marvel? 

She smiles with her eyes, with her heart, it’s so beautiful that I don’t know how anyone could hate her, I really don’t.

It’s not even that she’s beautiful, it’s literally just that she has a warm smile.
